{"id":"stoning","term":"Stoning","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A form of punishment (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Leviticus 20:2\">Lev. 20:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Leviticus 24:14\">24:14</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 13:10\">Deut. 13:10</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 17:5\">17:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 22:21\">22:21</a>) prescribed for certain offences. Of Achan (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 7:25\">Josh. 7:25</a>), Naboth (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 21\">1 Kings 21</a>), Stephen (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 7:59\">Acts 7:59</a>), Paul (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 14:19\">Acts 14:19</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Corinthians 11:25\">2 Cor. 11:25</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Leviticus 20:2","Leviticus 24:14","Deuteronomy 13:10","Deuteronomy 17:5","Deuteronomy 22:21","Joshua 7:25","1 Kings 21","Acts 7:59","Acts 14:19","2 Corinthians 11:25"]}